---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Customer Communication in Online Retail - More Personalization Pays Off - parcelLab"
  description="Proper communication with customers is increasingly important for online retailers. Here's how personalization, real-time contact, and shipping communication matter."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Research</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Customer Communication in Online Retail -- More Personalization Pays Off</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2019-08-16">August 16, 2019</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>4 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Proper communication with (potential) customers is increasingly important for online retailers. They should not forget that every customer is unique and has different needs and demands. So how can retailers do justice to every customer? One thing is clear: you can't make everyone happy. However, when it comes to customer communication, online retailers should keep a few basic things in mind.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">More Personalization and Appreciation</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Online retail is growing and growing -- but retailers must not forget their customers. Appreciation should no longer be exemplified only in brick-and-mortar retail, but is also becoming increasingly important in e-commerce. Personalized newsletters and mailings can address customers directly. It is also important that customer service is available at all times should problems or questions arise.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Customer Contact in Real Time</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          It is important that online retailers keep their customers informed in real time. Are there any innovations or has something important changed? Then merchants should inform their customers about it immediately. Real-time customer communication is becoming increasingly important, and this is no coincidence. Communication is becoming increasingly digital and faster.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          It is now possible to communicate with many companies via a chatbot integrated in Facebook Messenger. Lidl, for example, is focusing on even more innovation with the Chatbot LiA, which allows customers to find out about the shipping status of their package.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Don't Forget the Shipping</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Online retailers unfortunately often leave customers alone after sending the order. In doing so, they should also manage shipping communication themselves and not hand it over to the shipping service provider.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Key Finding</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--ink)]">The parcelLab E-Commerce Shipping Study found that 35% of the top 100 retailers send no message at all or only one message to their customers after shipping confirmation.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Customer communication is becoming increasingly digital and fast-paced. Customers expect online retailers to provide them with real-time information and answers. Those who manage to communicate proactively and personally with their customers will be rewarded -- with customer loyalty! However, customer communication shouldn't stop after the order is placed. Shipping and returns communication should also function smoothly. That's why online retailers should always handle this themselves and not leave it to the shipping service provider.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
